# Project Rules — Bit Link

## Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router), TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- Drizzle ORM + Postgres, ioredis, TanStack Query v5, Zod, Recharts
- Vercel deployment, Square Cloud for Postgres + Redis

## Critical Next.js 16 Conventions

- `proxy.ts` = Node.js interceptor (auth only, `/admin/:path*`)
- `[slug]/route.ts` = Node.js route handler for slug resolution + redirect
- No `middleware.ts` in this project — redirect does not run on Edge
- `"use cache"` directive — **not used** in this project (analytics queries flush a Redis buffer instead)
- `params` in pages and route handlers are async — always `await params`
- `after()` from `next/server` for fire-and-forget background tasks (replaces `waitUntil`)

## Code Conventions

- No `any`. No `as unknown as T`. TypeScript strict is not negotiable.
- All API inputs validated with Zod — shared schemas in `src/lib/validators/`
- Use `env.X` from `@/env` — never `process.env.X` directly
- Path aliases: `@/lib`, `@/components`, `@/db`, `@/env`
- Server-only modules must have `import 'server-only'` at the top

## Component Rules

- Default to Server Components. Add `"use client"` only when you need browser APIs, event handlers, or TanStack Query hooks.
- shadcn primitives live in `src/components/ui/` — do not modify them directly
- Business-logic components live in `src/components/{domain}/`

## Database Rules

- All Drizzle queries live in `src/lib/db/queries/` — not inline in route handlers
- Every mutable query must have a `.where()` clause
- Schema changes require: `bunx drizzle-kit generate` + `bunx drizzle-kit migrate`
- Cascade deletes defined at schema level, not application level

## Pagination Rules

- All list endpoints: cursor-based, `{ data: T[], nextCursor: string | null }`
- Cursor: `btoa(JSON.stringify({ createdAt, id }))`
- Client: `useInfiniteQuery` + `getNextPageParam: (last) => last.nextCursor ?? undefined`
- No offset pagination anywhere in the codebase

## Analytics Rules

- `trackClick()` always via `after()` — never awaited
- `trackClick()` writes to Redis pipeline (LPUSH + LTRIM), not directly to Postgres
- `flushClickBuffer()` batch-inserts from Redis to Postgres before analytics queries
- Errors in `trackClick` and `flushClickBuffer` are swallowed silently
- Never store raw User-Agent — only `sha256hex(ua)`
- Referrer: store full URL, display `new URL(referrer).hostname`

## Auth Rules

- Login rate-limited: 5 req/min per IP
- Admin API rate-limited: 60 req/min per IP
- POST/PATCH/DELETE on links require CSRF validation via `validateOrigin()`
- Logout uses Server Action (`logoutAction`), not an API route

## Git Rules

- Branch prefixes: `feature/` (human), `fix/` (bug fixes)
- All PRs target `main`
- Commit messages: `type(scope): description` — e.g. `feat(links): add expiry date field`
- No WIP commits on PRs — squash before requesting review
